# Kubectl — cluster config

Before any `kubectl` (pods, logs, events, etc.), set kubeconfig in same shell:

```bash
export KUBECONFIG=/Users/denisvolkov/Downloads/jaylinn.yaml
```

Then normal commands, e.g. `kubectl get pods -A`, `kubectl logs <pod> -n <ns> -c <container>`, `kubectl describe pod …`.

**Do not** assume default `~/.kube/config` for this cluster unless user says otherwise.
